article.headline: Marist 66, Canisius 44
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. (AP) -- Ryan Schneider scored 12 points and had 10 rebounds to lead Marist in a 66-44 win over Canisius Sunday. Jay Gavin and Ryan Stilphen each contributed 13 points for Marist (3-7, 7-2 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Spongy Benjamin added 10 points. It was Marist's thirteenth straight win at home. Frank Turner scored a team-high nine points and had five rebounds for Canisius (3-16, 1-8). Canisius shot 25.9 percent from the field and allowed Marist to score 21 second-chance points off 13 offensive rebounds. Marist shot 38.3 percent from the field and 36 percent from the 3-point range. Both teams had 41 rebounds.
